{"id":262,"html":263},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>Sokrates, the friend of all, lies here.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":262,"html":265},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Sokrates, l’amico di tutti, giace qui.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":267,"html":268},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>This epitaph has a formula very similar to pagan epitaphs, although the presence of the two Christograms denotes it as Christian. Ferrua and Korhonen read \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">πάντων φίλος\u003C/span> with the interpretation of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ο\u003C/span> as part of the Christogram, which in this case should be interpreted as \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ὁ Χ(ριστό)ς\u003C/span> (the same hight of the letter \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">O\u003C/span> compared to the other letters of the text is probably a misinterpretation of the stonecutter). However, there is no need to eliminate the article since other parallels of similar epithets denoting friendship and affection in Christian inscriptions, such as IMusCatania 178 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001359\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001359\u003C/a> and SEG 65. 791 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001633\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001633\u003C/a> present the names of the deceased followed by adjectives preceded by the article (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Κάλλιστος καὶ | Εὐκαρπία οἱ φιλόστορ|γοι\u003C/span> and \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ὁ πανφίλ|ητος ... Εὐδέμων\u003C/span> respectively).\u003C/p>  ",{"id":270,"html":271},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 1022 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000394\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000394\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1918 62 no.3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Agnello 1953 no.58) \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002211\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002211\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ferrua 1989 110 no.416 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 196 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":273,"html":274},"handnote"," \u003Cp>Regular letters with apices, lunate Ε and Σ, cursive Ω, A, Δ and Λ with extended serifs. Two Christograms at l. 2.\u003C/p> Lines 1-4  33-45  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not recorded  ",{"id":276,"html":277},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[279,281,284,286,289,290,293,294],{"html":280},"Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo, Alex Antoniou",{"id":282,"lang":122,"html":283},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σωκράτης\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σωκράτης\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Σωκράτης\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Σωκράτης\">Σωκράτης\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>☧ \u003Cspan data-text=\"πάντων\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"πᾶς\">πάντων\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ὁ\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"ὁ\">ὁ\u003C/spa